      "claim": "After substituting x = (t^2 - 1)/2, the inequality in step 4 simplifies to t^2(t - 3)(t + 3) < 0.",
      "reasoning": "Using x = (t^2 - 1)/2, we get 4x^2 = (t^2 - 1)^2 and 2x + 9 = t^2 + 8. Then the inequality becomes (t^2 - 1)^2 < (t^2 + 8)(1 - t)^2. Expanding and simplifying gives t^2(t^2 - 9) < 0, i.e. t^2(t - 3)(t + 3) < 0.",
